Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.03,0:01:17.26,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Producers\NMichihiko Suwa\N(Yomiuri TV)\NMasahito Yoshioka\N(Tokyo Movie)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.94,0:01:47.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yum!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.94,0:01:50.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ordering pizza was a good idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.25,0:01:55.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's for sure! We can't eat dinners like this when Dad's around!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.12,0:02:01.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He sure knows how to be careless, though! He forgot everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.16,0:02:03.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He must've been really happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.16,0:02:06.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been 10 years since he's seen his friend, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.03,0:02:09.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. He said he was going to drink like crazy,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.20,0:02:11.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so he'll be back late tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.60,0:02:14.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.10,0:02:17.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeesh! What bad timing!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.21,0:02:20.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I guess it {\i1}is{\i0} a company emergency.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.11,0:02:23.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We can get together another time soon. Bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.98,0:02:33.99,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Train #2 on the Tohto Loop Line will be arriving momentarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.99,0:02:37.22,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Please stand behind the yellow line for your safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.76,0:02:41.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's still only 7:30?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.76,0:02:45.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I should've gone somewhere for more drinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.72,0:03:12.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Six stops until Beika Station...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.73,0:03:25.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a10}"Beika"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.54,0:03:25.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Beika"...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.21,0:03:29.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.88,0:03:37.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That was close. I almost missed my stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.95,0:03:40.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Candy?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.76,0:03:43.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Was I eating this before?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.64,0:03:58.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What a poetic sight!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.09,0:04:20.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! It's you, Sachiko-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.76,0:04:24.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's me, Mouri! Kogoro Mouri!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.20,0:04:28.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember? We've met in the Poirot shop below my office!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.64,0:04:31.77,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Sachiko Shimamura (31)\NImport Company Manager
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.57,0:04:32.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the great detective, Kogoro Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.01,0:04:38.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! Come to think of it, isn't your apartment building near here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.71,0:04:40.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,8:00?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.15,0:04:43.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoops! I forgot my watch!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.38,0:04:47.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0}! Would you like to go for a drive?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.26,0:04:50.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I know a place with a beautiful night view!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.09,0:04:52.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's no fun unless you go with someone else!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.49,0:04:54.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Won't you come with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.20,0:04:56.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds great! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.53,0:04:58.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll pull the car out!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.35,0:05:17.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you cramped?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.59,0:05:21.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can pull the seat back.\NThere's a lever under the seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.09,0:05:23.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.86,0:05:25.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.70,0:05:33.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was working late by myself earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.74,0:05:39.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but I came back to check on my roommate, who caught a cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.24,0:05:41.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you need to go back to work, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.64,0:05:42.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.71,0:05:48.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hearing your exploits as a great detective would be even more useful!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.85,0:05:51.82,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I'm so glad he had an emergency come up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.82,0:05:54.55,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And the night is still young!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.27,0:06:05.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sachiko Shimamura
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.27,0:06:05.99,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazumi Takenaka
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.23,0:06:06.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I had so much fun tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.23,0:06:08.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I had a lot of fun, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.57,0:06:10.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, good night!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.64,0:06:12.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Good night!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.71,0:06:13.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.84,0:06:15.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.44,0:06:18.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The door... It's unlocked...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.13,0:06:33.85,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazumi Takenaka (29)\NAttendant
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.69,0:06:34.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The deceased is Kazumi Takenaka-{\i1}san{\i0}, a 29 year-old attendant.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.20,0:06:39.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0} and her roommate Sachiko Shimamura-{\i1}san{\i0} found her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.73,0:06:42.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Judging from the rigor mortis of her lower jaw and neck,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.90,0:06:49.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,she died approximately two-and-a-half hours ago, around 9:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.51,0:06:51.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.45,0:06:57.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri-{\i1}kun{\i0}! What are those two doing here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.09,0:06:59.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.09,0:07:03.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I called to let them know,\Nand they came here on their own!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.29,0:07:06.73,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What was Dad doing in a girl's home?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.76,0:07:12.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Sachiko-{\i1}san{\i0}'s room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.17,0:07:17.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It connects to the victim's room\Nvia dining room and kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.76,0:07:16.97,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,"Sachiko Shimamura"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.76,0:07:16.97,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,"Kazumi Takenaka"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.76,0:07:16.97,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,"Dining Room"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.51,0:07:21.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And, as you can see, this window is slightly open.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.41,0:07:25.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She says she might've forgotten to lock it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.15,0:07:28.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning the killer entered through this window?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.95,0:07:31.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But how would they get onto this balcony?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.99,0:07:33.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.62,0:07:35.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! That's dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.46,0:07:40.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See! You can jump onto the balcony from the emergency stairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.03,0:07:42.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you're doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.63,0:07:47.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The intruder probably didn't realize\NKazumi-{\i1}san{\i0} was sick in bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.94,0:07:51.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, during a search for things of value in the kitchen,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.21,0:07:54.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the sound woke Kazumi-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.08,0:07:57.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the thief stabbed her out of surprise!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.21,0:07:59.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And then the intruder escaped through the front door.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.75,0:08:02.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, it was a robbery-murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.32,0:08:04.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It would seem so.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.35,0:08:08.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry to ask, but where were you at around 9:00?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.89,0:08:13.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At that time, I was taking a drive with Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.13,0:08:15.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?! With Mouri-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.50,0:08:17.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.13,0:08:20.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Dad! Weren't you meeting a friend tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.23,0:08:25.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I did meet him, but something came up, so we ended early.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.64,0:08:31.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So I returned to Beika Station, strolled around 2nd Street to sober up,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.48,0:08:34.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then ran into Sachiko-{\i1}san{\i0} behind Beika Middle School,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.58,0:08:37.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,as she was getting into her car!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.32,0:08:39.32,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Behind the middle school?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.32,0:08:40.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When was this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.42,0:08:45.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right at 8:00. Then we both went for a drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.59,0:08:50.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She knew a nice spot with a good view of the Tohto Bay Bridge,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.30,0:08:53.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and we arrived there at about 8:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.27,0:08:56.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We chatted for about an hour and a half
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.30,0:09:01.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,while we drank beer and juice\Nshe bought from a vending machine,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.18,0:09:03.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then left at around 10:10.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.74,0:09:07.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We stopped by her office for about five minutes,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.25,0:09:12.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then arrived here at about 10:50.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.69,0:09:16.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's when we found the body and contacted you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.56,0:09:19.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning you're her...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.30,0:09:22.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! I'm witness to her alibi!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.00,0:09:26.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, what were you doing with Mouri-{\i1}kun{\i0} behind Beika Middle School?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.77,0:09:31.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I run a small import company in Akebono.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.81,0:09:34.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was working late by myself tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.61,0:09:38.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I was worried about Kazumi,\Nsince she was in bed with a cold,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.38,0:09:42.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so I came back to check on her at around 7:50.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.92,0:09:46.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see Kazumi-{\i1}san{\i0} then?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.69,0:09:50.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't really talk to her; she was fast asleep,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.26,0:09:53.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so I left her alone and went straight back to my car.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.79,0:09:57.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say. Why did you park your car\Nbehind the middle school?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.63,0:09:58.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.67,0:10:01.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you use the apartment building's parking lot?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.90,0:10:05.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Our parking lot is a two-level, top-bottom type, so it's a pain to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.81,0:10:08.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And I planned to return to my office right after.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.34,0:10:11.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then couldn't you park in front of the apartment building?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.51,0:10:15.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I would have gotten in the way\Nof the buses that pass by the front.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.89,0:10:23.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"To Sachiko Shimamura"...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.39,0:10:25.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is addressed to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.11,0:10:25.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.83,0:10:28.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When did this package arrive?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.63,0:10:29.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.56,0:10:33.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Was it here when you came to check on Kazumi-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.47,0:10:35.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.84,0:10:41.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood. We'll check with the delivery people tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.78,0:10:49.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Something really bothers me...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.68,0:10:52.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? The fish bones?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.25,0:10:56.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not that. The reason Sachiko-{\i1}san{\i0} parked her car behind Beika Middle School.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.96,0:10:59.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.36,0:11:01.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you talk about for an hour and a half
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.36,0:11:05.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,at the Bay Bridge view point?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.13,0:11:09.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And why did you go on a drive with her, anyway?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.00,0:11:10.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad! Don't tell me you two—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.94,0:11:15.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What are you trying to say?!\NI didn't do anything improper!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.41,0:11:17.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then tell me what you talked about!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.95,0:11:22.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't remember everything we said!\NBesides, halfway through—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.65,0:11:23.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Halfway through... what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.82,0:11:25.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, uhh...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.09,0:11:26.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.76,0:11:32.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is, we only chatted for the first half hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.89,0:11:35.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I fell deep asleep after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.56,0:11:36.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You fell asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.96,0:11:41.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Drunkenness started to set in while I had those beers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.47,0:11:45.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was after 10:00 when she woke me up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.21,0:11:54.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's so funny! You fell asleep during a date!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.25,0:11:56.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit laughing! Sheesh!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.35,0:11:58.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I didn't want to say anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.79,0:12:01.52,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He fell asleep halfway through?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.52,0:12:05.59,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But he was awake until 9:00, chatting with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.59,0:12:10.33,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The murder took place around 9:00. Her alibi is airtight.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.33,0:12:11.70,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.70,0:12:15.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. You forgot your watch yesterday, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.34,0:12:17.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How did you know the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.87,0:12:19.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw the clock in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.87,0:12:22.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What about before then?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.01,0:12:26.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There was a clock in the bar,\Nand I saw a clock at Shibahama Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.38,0:12:28.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What time was it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.22,0:12:29.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,7:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.58,0:12:31.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,7:30?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.69,0:12:35.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's 15 minutes from Shibahama Station to Beika Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.86,0:12:40.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's 10 minutes by foot from Beika Station to Beika Middle School.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.06,0:12:43.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means you ran into Sachiko-{\i1}san{\i0} at around...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.53,0:12:46.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I already told you! 8:00 exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.60,0:12:49.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard the clock in a nearby house ring!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.64,0:12:52.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now eat your damn food and go to school!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.44,0:12:53.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.97,0:12:57.38,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He's right. I should just forget about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.15,0:13:07.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Three laps around the schoolyard is really exhausting!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.15,0:13:09.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't go on...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.12,0:13:11.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a little more! Hang in there, Genta!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.49,0:13:15.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Thinking about something you like makes it go quicker!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.13,0:13:16.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Something I like?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.86,0:13:19.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! I'm gonna have boxed eel lunch tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.67,0:13:21.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Boxed eel lunch! Boxed eel lunch! Tonight—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.60,0:13:24.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Genta! We're done now!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.00,0:13:27.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no. He's too busy thinking about boxed eel lunches.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.21,0:13:29.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet he's going to do another lap!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.88,0:13:34.71,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Could it be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.65,0:13:40.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,One trip around the Loop Line?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.92,0:13:46.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you have fallen asleep after you got on at Shibahama Station?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.90,0:13:49.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A trip around the Loop Line takes an hour!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.30,0:13:52.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you had gone around it once while you were asleep,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.77,0:13:59.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you would've reached Beika Station at 8:40 instead of 7:40!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.07,0:14:03.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nonsense! I only slept for 15 minutes! I couldn't have looped around!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.61,0:14:06.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's see for ourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.05,0:14:07.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.18,0:14:10.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's all ride the Loop Line tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.12,0:14:14.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In the same train and train car leaving Shibahama Station at 7:30!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.66,0:14:18.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that'll be fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.10,0:14:29.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Dad? Remember anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.94,0:14:34.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I guess I was pretty out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.01,0:14:36.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But she can't be the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.08,0:14:39.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's just take a full trip around. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.79,0:14:50.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the furthest stop from Shibahama Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.30,0:15:03.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it? Do you know that man?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.91,0:15:05.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Candy!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.94,0:15:09.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was sleeping with his mouth wide open yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.11,0:15:14.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...so he tossed a piece of candy in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.85,0:15:20.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What time was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.32,0:15:23.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The same as today. Around 8:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.66,0:15:28.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means I arrived at Beika Station just before 9:00!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.46,0:15:32.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And that I ran into Sachiko-{\i1}san{\i0} at 9:00!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.05,0:15:35.81,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Real Time
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.05,0:15:35.81,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,False Time
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.27,0:15:36.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! You arrived at the Tohto Bay Bridge view point at 9:30!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.77,0:15:38.68,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Real Time
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.77,0:15:38.68,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,False Time
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.77,0:15:39.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you chatted for 30 minutes, until 10:00!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.64,0:15:41.35,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Real Time
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.64,0:15:41.35,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,False Time
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.77,0:15:42.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And then you woke up at 10:10!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.31,0:15:46.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were wrong about sleeping for an hour and 10 minutes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.41,0:15:49.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You only slept for 10 minutes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.75,0:15:53.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, she turned the clock back an hour
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.15,0:15:57.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to use me for her alibi...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.19,0:16:01.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Last night, she parked her car in this out-of-the-way location
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.43,0:16:04.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and left to kill the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.27,0:16:08.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She entered through the window she had unlocked in advance,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.24,0:16:10.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,made sound on purpose,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.24,0:16:15.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then killed the awoken victim to make it look like a robbery-murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.65,0:16:21.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, she returned here and ran into you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.25,0:16:26.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, she...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.12,0:16:32.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Were they the bloodied clothes and gloves she used in the murder?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.86,0:16:39.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If so, then she disposed of them at the view point while you slept.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.70,0:16:43.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She set the car clock an hour ahead before you got in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.97,0:16:47.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, while you were asleep, she put it back to normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.28,0:16:52.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it! How dare she toy with the great Kogoro Mouri?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.08,0:16:54.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Was there anything else out of the ordinary?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.19,0:17:01.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The children saw Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.69,0:17:04.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your alibi no longer holds.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.43,0:17:11.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You met Mouri-{\i1}kun{\i0} behind Beika Middle School just after the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.23,0:17:17.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But isn't it possible the children mistook Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.51,0:17:20.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,for someone else who looks similar?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.08,0:17:22.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That possibility does exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.21,0:17:26.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if by some chance my alibi doesn't check out,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.18,0:17:30.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that doesn't mean that {\i1}I{\i0} killed Kazumi-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.55,0:17:36.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's correct. But there {\i1}is{\i0} proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.13,0:17:40.19,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I leave it in your hands today, old guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.83,0:17:47.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you recognize this pen?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.30,0:17:50.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It's your pen, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.81,0:17:52.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.71,0:17:54.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you alright, Mouri-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.88,0:17:58.74,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh, geez! Do I have to do it after all?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.18,0:18:04.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let us go back to 8:30 PM two nights ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.95,0:18:10.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A deliveryman knocked on the door,\Nand Kazumi-{\i1}san{\i0} answered it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.66,0:18:13.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,However, she couldn't find her ink stamp.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.36,0:18:15.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,With no other choice,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.23,0:18:18.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,she decided to sign for it with a pen in the dining room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.97,0:18:21.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it wouldn't write.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.10,0:18:24.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Supposedly, the deliveryman said it might be the ink,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.87,0:18:29.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so he took the pen and looked inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.11,0:18:37.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Some ink was still left, and when she tried to write again, it worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.12,0:18:43.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When the deliveryman left, Kazumi-{\i1}san{\i0} placed the pen by the phone
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.66,0:18:46.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and returned to her room to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.90,0:18:49.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Twenty minutes later...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.47,0:18:57.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Seeing your own pen lying next to her body
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.87,0:19:02.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,right after you killed her,\Nyou instinctively picked it up and...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.42,0:19:13.44,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh! It's you, Sachiko-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.96,0:19:18.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Afterward, you invited me for a drive
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.93,0:19:21.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and moved the clothes and gloves under the passenger seat
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.73,0:19:24.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to under the back seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.30,0:19:28.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When you did, the pen in your pocket fell out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.91,0:19:37.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't seem to notice, but after I got into the passenger seat,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.78,0:19:42.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I dropped a pen from my suit, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.92,0:19:45.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I assume you can guess what happened next.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.12,0:19:51.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What I picked up was your pen instead of mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.63,0:20:00.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We found the fingerprints of you and Mouri-{\i1}kun{\i0} on this pen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.54,0:20:07.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In addition, the fingerprints of the deliveryman were on the ink stick.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.34,0:20:12.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,These fingerprints mean you entered the apartment after 8:30!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.95,0:20:14.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.19,0:20:22.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazumi was blackmailing me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.26,0:20:31.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,One year ago, I unknowingly imported and sold outlawed goods.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.17,0:20:36.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazumi knew this, and demanded\NI pay her a set amount each month.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.37,0:20:41.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She threatened to tell the banks and cut off my financing if I said no,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.98,0:20:44.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so I did as she said.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.85,0:20:48.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But when I considered being blackmailed for the rest of my life...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.62,0:20:50.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You decided to kill her at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.92,0:20:52.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.39,0:20:58.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0} called out to me,\NI thought I was already done for.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.03,0:21:02.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I realized he thought it was an hour earlier than it really was
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.06,0:21:04.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and decided to use that to my advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.10,0:21:10.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But what did you plan to do for an alibi if he hadn't shown up?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.04,0:21:12.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I set a video camera in my office window
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.51,0:21:15.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and recorded the pub across the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.61,0:21:19.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I planned to tell the police it was one of the customers leaving
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.81,0:21:21.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,at the time of the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.65,0:21:25.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So you stopped by your office after your drive with Mouri-{\i1}kun{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.05,0:21:28.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to take down that video camera?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.42,0:21:33.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The rest is all as Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0} deduced.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.56,0:21:36.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for all the trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.39,0:23:15.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say. Can I ask you one thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.16,0:23:20.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You could've killed him after he fell asleep at the view point, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.10,0:23:22.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.17,0:23:26.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But you didn't. How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.29,0:23:33.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't hold anything against Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0}, after all.
